The paper deals with the conversion of artificial recurrent neural networks to spiking neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents a methodology for training and constraining the neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of low-power neuromorphic hardware, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET) and systems and control (cs.SY).
